{"key":"processedPost-13841248","value":{"id":13841248,"first":13840981,"last":13983452,"when":1295887559,"utime":"01/24/11 06:45 PM","content":"A few points here.&nbsp; I've used regular coffee and decaf coffee and both perform equally.&nbsp; It's not the caffeine that provides the boost.<br /><br />Don't sterilize the coffee grinds unless you intend to keep the substrate sterile until full colonization.&nbsp; Mix the spent(after brewing) coffee grinds into the bulk substrate material, bring to field capacity moisture content, and pasteurize at 140F/60C for 90 minutes.<br /><br />Never add liquid coffee to substrates and never use fresh coffee grinds that have not been used to brew a pot of coffee.<br /><br />Coffee does not decrease colonization times.&nbsp; If anything, adding nutritious additives to a bulk substrate slows down speed of colonization, but does increase yields.<br />RR","title":"Re: Coir...seeking opinions, especially from trusted cultivators","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}